    <div class="container" id="about">
        <h1 class="text-center">About Us</h1>
        <br>
        <p>
            Incandescence is the Annual Socio-Cultural Festival of National Institute of Technology Silchar. Whilst marking four days of absolute ecstasy, Incandescence is an avenue to be comforted from the routine life and to embrace the fun and frolic embedded
            with tantalizing performances and exciting competitions. Over the years, it has managed to carve a niche for itself among its peer aesthetic and ethnic events with the participation of more than 20,000 people. From showcasing talent on The
            Ramp on the Glitterati night, dancing your heart out to the metallic tunes during Thundermarch to getting indulged into serious debating in Deprador, there's something in store for everyone. This time we have decided to make our festival more
            relishing than ever before and transcend the contemporary times! The theme of Incandescence’20 'A Royal Indian Carnival', refers collectively to the thousands of distinct and unique cultures of religions and communities all over India, from
            the Rajputana lifestyle in north-western India to the tribalway of life in north-eastern India to the Sangam literature in southern India.<br>
            <b>The Campus Ambassador Program is open for all college students irrespective of their college and their fields. All you need that you are a college student!</b>

        </p>
